1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:04,170
A code tells you how a passage was classified.

2
00:00:04,170 --> 00:00:08,715
A research memo records the analytical reasoning around that decision:

3
00:00:08,715 --> 00:00:13,259
what you noticed, what changed and what evidence might challenge

4
00:00:13,259 --> 00:00:14,168
the interpretation.

5
00:00:14,568 --> 00:00:18,988
Open Memo and place it near the relevant source or code.

6
00:00:18,988 --> 00:00:23,006
A useful memo names the emerging idea, records uncertainty and

7
00:00:23,006 --> 00:00:27,025
ends with a next action such as comparing another case

8
00:00:27,025 --> 00:00:28,632
or revisiting a definition.

9
00:00:29,032 --> 00:00:32,131
The canvas lets you arrange reasoning spatially.

10
00:00:32,131 --> 00:00:36,559
Keep a memo close to the evidence it interprets, and

11
00:00:36,559 --> 00:00:40,986
use groups carefully so organisation supports the argument rather than

12
00:00:40,986 --> 00:00:41,872
replacing it.

13
00:00:42,272 --> 00:00:45,877
The Ethics view helps keep governance questions visible.

14
00:00:45,877 --> 00:00:50,382
Record the boundaries that matter to the study, but remember

15
00:00:50,382 --> 00:00:54,888
that software prompts do not replace consent terms, ethics approval

16
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:56,240
or institutional policy.

17
00:00:56,640 --> 00:01:01,213
The Tools menu gathers supporting views for methods and quality work.

18
00:01:01,213 --> 00:01:05,371
Use excerpts and the codebook to inspect evidence, and generate

19
00:01:05,371 --> 00:01:09,529
a methods statement only after confirming that it accurately describes

20
00:01:09,529 --> 00:01:10,776
what you did.

21
00:01:11,176 --> 00:01:15,720
Exported reports can support supervision, team review or writing.

22
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:20,769
When AI was used, include the relevant disclosure and retain

23
00:01:20,769 --> 00:01:24,808
the human decisions behind accepted or rejected suggestions.

24
00:01:25,208 --> 00:01:28,850
You do not need to document every click.

25
00:01:28,850 --> 00:01:33,402
Document the decisions that changed the analysis: the reason, the

26
00:01:33,402 --> 00:01:35,678
evidence and any later revision.

27
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:39,320
That is the trail another researcher can follow.
